how to teach dwarf hammsters not to bite out of my dwarf hamsters bites alot and how can a teach it of pick it up so it wont bite first you must learn the cause of the biting it is to defend themselves right hamsters actually rarely bite their first instinct is to run and hide but when you are holding them they cannot do that so they resort to biting they are scared remember this when you get frustrated it's important to be calm and move slowly so from now on place your hand in the cage with a small treat on your palm position your hand so they have to climb on your hand to get the food so they'll probablky grab it and run let them do this daily for a while then start holding the treat in one hand with your original hand in the cage for climbing as they come for the food draw it further so they venture more and more this teaches them that you are a source of food and not harmful or dangerous at all also never grab them always lift them with two hands cupped around provide that there is no loud noise as this will only stress them and handle them daily no less Hamster Dog training Domestic rabbit Brown Bear Skateboarding trick Professional wrestling throws Pet skunk Guinea pig Tag Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Spider Magic (illusion) StarCraft: Uprising Professional wrestling holds Aikido Suplex Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Urinary incontinence Hansel und Gretel Snake charming Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Professional wrestling aerial techniques Swingout The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Drizzt Do'Urden Spider-Man Glossary of climbing terms Boy Scouts of America Ferret Pok__mon Live! Internal ballistics Rugby union Powerbomb The Empty Child Swimming Rayden Fancy rat RuneScape quests Survival skills Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Tenshinhan The Death Gate Cycle Professional wrestling double-team maneuvers Kender Cat Gesture The Legend of Zelda series enemies Spanking Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Professional wrestling match